Adult Listener Ratings

ggplot(data=rw.merge, aes(x=rating, color=transc))+geom_density(size=2)+
  scale_colour_manual(values=cbPalette) + theme_tufte()

The wr line is really flat which means the adult listeners ratings of wr transcriptions is suspect/unreliable.

You have ws, and you have rs, and if you have even a little bit of rhoticity, then people perceive it towards the /r/ side. /r/ bias.

Need to check the method of transcription here, as theres some debate about how to group the transcriptions. People may perceive this is just R, W, or a half r, with some rhoticity but not full on. What does wr mean?

R makes sense. W makes sense. RW also makes sense. Its an R with a pinch of W. People arent quite as sure with RW as the R, but its pretty R like. The professional said this is neither r nor w but more r like, but the adult rates pushed them strongly towards R, but not fully so.
